RockNES seems OK.<br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />To save 16 cycles during vblank.<br /><br />To eliminate unofficial opcodes as a factor in the test, I have added a second build-time option called <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">AVOID_UNOFFICIAL_OPCODES</tt>, in addition to the existing build-time option called <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">NESTOPIA_WORKAROUND</tt>, and built two more ROMs without unofficial opcodes, one with and one without the Nestopia workarounds. The ROMs built without unofficial opcodes behave (or misbehave) the same way in Mednafen as the corresponding ROMs with unofficial opcodes.<br /></div><br /><br />Works fine in RockNES now. The Nestopia version flashes the bottom of the image (around 40 or more lines).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=39">Zepper</a> — Wed Mar 04, 2015 7:11 pm</p><hr />
