<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Trying to get FME-7 IRQs right]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12436&amp;p=142246#p142246"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Here's another test specifically for the acknowledgment behaviors I'm seeing. No unofficial opcodes.<br /><br />The demo tries to acknowledge the interrupt in one of six ways:<br /><ul><li>Writing value of $00, $01, $80, or $81 to register $0D </li><li>Writing value of $FF to register $0E or $0F </li></ul><br />These are the results I get:<br /><ul><li>FCEUX: all Acked </li><li>Mednafen: 0D=00 and 0D=01 Acked; others No ack </li><li>PowerPak: 0D=00 and 0D=80 Acked; others No ack </li></ul><br />EDIT: I mentioned it on #nesdev.<br /><ul><li>tpw_rules tried it on Everdrive and got the same result as PowerPak </li></ul><br /></div><br /><br /><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-pwJvIuv7nSg/VPJ52BZSHHI/AAAAAAAAIQY/NTPMYC-CxWQ/s800/TV2015022823263400.jpg" alt="Image" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4943">l_oliveira</a> — Sat Feb 28, 2015 7:42 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
